# ZeroClaw environment (loaded by zeroclaw binary at startup)
# Copy to ~/.zeroclaw/zeroclaw.env and customize.
# Works for direct run (zeroclaw daemon) and service (Linux systemd / macOS launchd).
# Supports $HOME expansion. Never commit zeroclaw.env — it may contain secrets.

# ── Logging (RUST_LOG) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Enables tracing so "Task failed" and other errors appear in journalctl.
# RUST_LOG=zeroclaw=info
# RUST_LOG=zeroclaw=debug,tower_http=debug

# ── PATH for user-installed tools ───────────────────────────────
# Override default PATH. Include Python, Node, conda, etc.
# PATH=$HOME/.local/bin:$HOME/.pyenv/shims:$HOME/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin:$HOME/miniconda3/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

# ── Extra vars for shell tool ───────────────────────────────────
# Also add to config.toml [autonomy] shell_env_passthrough if needed.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://...
# MY_APP_KEY=...
